{"id": "8be3aa05f33c01c5d24d38bc35df6caf0ef01c0e12765e6a636065189908155d", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:0", "text": "This nodes allows artists to place patterns using a 3D projection as opposed to a 2D solution often used for textures reliant on UVs. This allows selection of Pref (for deforming meshes) and specification of a coordinate system to transform to."}
{"id": "f102986b39effb31080ae442f61febe7ed58df1515c0711ccfadfe0311ccec81", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:2", "text": "Scale"}
{"id": "57caaae863c454be1208dad3283238ba9eb966648077ecddc0090b3f640badcc", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:3", "text": "Scale the frequency of the feature uniformly in 3D."}
{"id": "b43b4b5eed3bd419d70312125e292b4f75a847bd1d048887e09dd0011d97b40a", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:5", "text": "Select the type of position you want to use."}
{"id": "8d59829c1e15afe1a7fae93e8e5e32d8511bec5fd598a09f4fea6033b31e8a66", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:6", "text": "Usage"}
{"id": "8e37953d23daca5ff01b8282c33f4e0a2152f1d1885f94c06418617e3ee1d24e", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:7", "text": "Value"}
{"id": "4e75423cb7643b0da7ab3da2d16e0831bd5d1130812387b83c4ddcb2f352c7fc", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:8", "text": "Default variable"}
{"id": "18ec820bf8dcf2b0a01b55638bff1977ea7a240cf7e8d9ff4c57251216852155", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:9", "text": "Current position: P"}
{"id": "5754addaf5911578d9bf115263359b13de0e537eff0dd14ec6548709490ae311", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:10", "text": "Use the current (displaced) surface position"}
{"id": "d36549bd5b82f1f5520772454a5d3651c2369818b56ea511e3f3ca71a71efc08", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:11", "text": "Undisplaced position: Po"}
{"id": "ff978c35a702d7c0ba1670dd50d42f80f1efbf9d17f6e4c240bd4a648273a0d5", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:12", "text": "Use the surface position"}
{"id": "6db7d803e74f1ffa7d8f5adc0bf95b3e15bf4c8373fffadf546227cc6c6742cb", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:13", "text": "before"}
{"id": "4d94d77305562a29d5299fd3c28a21f7d2cb0f0f8681d71a64d2ddb2f5d2dbac", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:14", "text": "it was displaced"}
{"id": "1419b38716afb25ce89d64bd88006fc0cfcdf1dac05e188ee4be7498ffcff4ca", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:15", "text": "Deform : __Pref"}
{"id": "65b0fdf57e277549a863b9ab0090bda13b4d2f4cfcaf34c4c5f5a3d473cbcbe7", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:16", "text": "Use a reference position primitive variable in object space"}
{"id": "2f4a5b034c898054c0156b207fd5e134a5a9513e37c7016818be983b2506a65e", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:17", "text": "Deform & transform: __WPref"}
{"id": "25fe93c46e161809f4dd9600a9ab23c7ba703ae70ef48a3de55971fc67f27c22", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:18", "text": "Use a reference position primitive variable in world space"}
{"id": "487647c574cd75e45f2116f0fb3b40dedfa8993cbb7ed1ebc9f8040f6acd1bee", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:19", "text": "You can only use"}
{"id": "83fc64d737338451fc9aabe94c52d41aa8dd2293fd4e85f86c1e01e0f6eac9b1", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:21", "text": "if these primitive variables have been attached to your geometry using your bridge product. Typically known as a Reference or Rest pose. Note that these are just names, the underlying bridge product provides the data as named, not the pattern node. If using a procedural such as Alembic, be sure the data has Pref baked into the objects on export."}
{"id": "c229dc79d74bda0086fc38a46c988d2b857156cd50614ed2f104a97bde056c84", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:22", "text": "Why use the un-displaced position ?"}
{"id": "33cf779fdb3cd84454dfd45fa3d6caf87973a20c5c41d77d89a30a0f143d5437", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:23", "text": "When using the same 3d noise in the BxDF and the displacement, you should use Po to make sure the patterns are lining up."}
{"id": "6da94174e57953caefa056edbe4464a689cba8828d28db8677be5eeb0fe0fc0e", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:24", "text": "Pref"}
{"id": "211bd171002586a7978af58daec5d20c3ee5e8daca872120da1d1d19d327c625", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:25", "text": "Name of geometry Pref (Maya uses __Pref and __WPref)."}
{"id": "e74ea08cfba235dc2ecb51aa5e5432024dbe0efdffe62d857b07abb01eca8884", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:26", "text": "This field is only used when"}
{"id": "a87d7b22807950dcaa04da72ddb56517edecd800ac216270f4dfdb3db3a5e94c", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:28", "text": "is set to \""}
{"id": "59974c3262dbe9bfd4e47201806bc3bb5a630258ddbb078dec8289b21084c3ba", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:29", "text": "Deform : __Pref\""}
{"id": "6194be286a138396f1fcba47727280a77a09cbc2d105425681e55b0aeae80283", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:31", "text": "\"Deform & transform: __WPref\""}
{"id": "21f08fd2d45b80b119581b5c11d40dfac7d48d0cf3dbecfb43177d13c23729dc", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:33", "text": "If left empty, we assume either"}
{"id": "3b606c9b58731adfed73fb84ffd57e47e6e3fdf373022e3fc367a60a842153f8", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:35", "text": ", based on the current"}
{"id": "c6f5b48f4d761c635f40e150a8f9c941288070f606ee9d5d8c35e21986f1e328", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:37", "text": "settings."}
{"id": "b514ebf73921fea11670ca9640e96c27bc4e980867839d368eca5bd872bd174f", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:38", "text": "Coordinate System"}
{"id": "b8de9a58642202c40a976d0cf656641568dc5c2f2e4e04ca24f07412ac3c9543", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:39", "text": "Name of a coordinate system transform to apply to the manifold. (Maya calls these place3d nodes)."}
{"id": "be7bebad30a33d81c8545e7ef5230faee4ea1c58bd27e937de7616bc881681fb", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:40", "text": "If left empty, we use the position in"}
{"id": "8ba9647d9dc0354acdb1c67c8c0eeb246bd2cb9017659cc24e49755f8bc93014", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:41", "text": "object-space"}
{"id": "8870de0df0ccdada725d2dbd90d263477f52acae9d1556a93bf335052256e335", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:42", "text": ", as this is what you need for"}
{"id": "4bc4a7f7d071e8630e9adbe38a1faa7230f9b91367e023014e85669a17037d12", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:43", "text": "non-deforming"}
{"id": "9e92fb4d5be54fdeb80c142a6f22b9ed941700b3591452c79a204d6fb2de68ee", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:44", "text": "objects."}
{"id": "3db7c958dfdf5ab8d6e5874200dba26597b825229e0ae2e1ba3fd74632f54aa8", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:45", "text": "Warp"}
{"id": "01d69f09d9fc084d389a28ad9937f2d6cedf45a0e3450eb852866c0071b67b0b", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:46", "text": "Connect a noise or texture to warp the domain"}
{"id": "c8868ef373a3f6688368a7c1564cc04c78f4f1ba69fe99a3acfd61819f0ca3cf", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:47", "text": "Warp amount"}
{"id": "4ead2ce6ed752662062f46858ca5957d7d59ddba956246dcafce06d2413bfbba", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:48", "text": "Slider control the amount of warp"}
{"id": "f6a214f7a5fcda0c2cee9660b7fc29f5649e3c68aad48e20e950137c98913a68", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:50", "text": "result"}
{"id": "410cd3cef62b2e902752ea6e43ddf90f78f95a3b5d23bac86ed793bdb2bc8d42", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:51", "text": "The 3D manifold."}
{"id": "aa502315570fa2a9c0d9ee32993d204185f0bc160ec0a841105326c24111977e", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:53", "text": "A float representation of the X component of the manifold."}
{"id": "e45c354baf56767f0b230b1695bb2654aeed9d96ddbf2d62c4fcb54551ef26a0", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:55", "text": "A float representation of the Y component of the manifold."}
{"id": "0b2eed571c05fbf7debf7d26e255271429c69719fdbc122e575146357ccf3802", "item_id": "0b0b27a43e:57", "text": "A float representation of the Z component of the manifold."}
